1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,880
Morning, Dwight.

2
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:11,880
Who are you?

3
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:13,320
Who am I?

4
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:14,520
I'm Jim.

5
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:17,040
We've been working together for 12 years.

6
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,840
Weird job, Dwight.

7
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:19,840
You're not Jim.

8
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:20,840
Jim's not Asian.

9
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:22,480
You seriously never noticed?

10
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:28,120
Hey, hats off to you for not seeing race.

11
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:29,120
Alright then, Jim.

12
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:34,160
Why don't you tell me about that sale that you made yesterday?

13
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:38,360
Wellington Systems sold them 10 cases of 24 pound letter stock.

14
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:41,320
Or were you talking about Krieger Murphy because I didn't close that one yet.

15
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:46,720
But I'm hoping I've got a voicemail from Paul Krieger waiting for me.

16
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:53,840
Please enter your password.

17
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:55,520
You have one new message.

18
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:56,520
How did you know?

19
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:57,520
No, no, no.

20
00:00:57,920 --> 00:01:01,480
That is sensitive information only for employees, not outsiders.

21
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:02,480
Dwight, cut it out.

22
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:03,480
I'm trying to work.

23
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:04,480
You don't work here.

24
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,480
You're not Jim.

25
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:07,320
Jim, I got us that dinner reservation.

26
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:08,320
Grieco 730.

27
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:13,320
Oh great, can't wait.

28
00:01:13,320 --> 00:01:16,760
Jim's at the dentist this morning and Steve is an actor friend of ours.

29
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:21,280
I don't know who you are, but you are not Jim.

30
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:24,280
This is Jim.

31
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:30,040
Oh, how did...

32
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:57,040
Hey, study buddies.

33
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:59,640
Oh, okay.

34
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,640
Getting things done.

35
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,640
Awesome.

36
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:04,360
It's all about finding ways to make yourself more efficient.

37
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,360
Life hacking, baby.

38
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:09,920
This morning, I brushed my teeth in the shower, saved myself 90 seconds, which I just used

39
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:11,560
to explain this to you.

40
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,560
Damn it.

41
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:16,520
Since Andy promoted me to assistant regional manager, I've been trying to step up my game,

42
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,520
be more productive.

43
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,040
In fact, you know what?

44
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:22,280
Let's knock out a few more of these soundbites while we're here.

45
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,480
Whoa.

46
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:27,480
That person has found him or herself in quite a predicament.

47
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:30,480
Woo hoo, that Toby.

48
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:32,480
When will he ever learn?

49
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:35,480
Andy, Andy, Andy.

50
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:38,480
I can't believe Kevin swallowed a pen.

51
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:42,480
I can't believe Kevin swallowed another pen.

52
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:57,480
Oscar, Oscar, Oscar.

53
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:02,480
Thanks.

54
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:05,480
Totally my fault.

55
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,480
What are you doing?

56
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:12,480
What?

57
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,480
French.

58
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:27,480
It's a great language.

59
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:30,480
If you're a chain-smoking acrobat.

60
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:33,480
I'm just trying to fit in better with Andy's family.

61
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:36,480
They all speak more than one language, usually when I'm there.

62
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,480
You want to learn a really impressive second language?

63
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:39,480
Try Dothraki.

64
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,480
Win over any man in my guild.

65
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:46,480
Dothraki is the native tongue of the nomadic, warmongering horse lords of Essos, as featured

66
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:49,480
in the superb home box office series Game of Thrones.

67
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:54,480
It has a lot of nudity, which I fast-forward through to get to the chopped-off heads.

68
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:56,480
I could teach you if you want.

69
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:57,480
It's a lot easier than French.

70
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,480
Yeah, let's do it.

71
00:03:58,480 --> 00:03:59,480
Athavrosar!

72
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:01,480
It means excellent.

73
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:03,480
And we have begun.

74
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,480
Is everything okay?

75
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,480
Oh, oh yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

76
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:12,480
Fine, fine, fine, fine.

77
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:17,480
I mean, I just don't want to burden you with my massive stress freak-outs.

78
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,480
Great.

79
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:23,480
It's just that I am taking my driver's license test in two days, and I need to practice with

80
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:25,480
an experienced driver in the car.

81
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:29,480
But I've had no time to do that, thanks to Demandee.

82
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:37,480
I just want to hit the open road and drive, man, but in whose car?

83
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,480
Nellie!

84
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:42,480
Get your wrinkly old balls in here.

85
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:49,480
Nellie, I could practice with you in my car at lunchtime.

86
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,480
Oh, Pan, thank you.

87
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:53,480
You are my savior.

88
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,480
I'm sorry.
